When you install Docker on a Linux host you're actually installing three different competenece

Docker Engine

Docker Daemon-->Is the background process that manages objects such as the images conatainers volumes and networks
REST API-->Is the API Interface that programs can use to talk to the daemon and provide instructions
Docker CLI-->Command Line Interface to perform action run destroy stop start

containerization

Namespace

Process ID
Unix timesharing
Mount
Interprocess
Network

cgroups

docker run --cpu=.5 ubuntu
docker run --memory=100m ubuntu
Linux system
Docker container
